description:
"The Present Truth," a publication dating back to 1849 and a precursor to the Adventist Church, aimed to unify people under the guidance of James and Ellen White. Media, at the time, played a crucial role in shaping the early stages of the Adventist movement.

Listen to the full episode of ANN In-Depth, where Justin Kim shares reflections about the history of Adventist Review. 

https://youtu.be/Y3OZ-nd_uWc
